{
  "doc": "A free-running synthesized step-sequenced beatmaker (V1.3 Toy 1, ADR-0022). Three lanes — kick, snare, hat — each a 16-step boolean gate sequencer (gate_mode=1) driving a one-voice drum synth built entirely from operators (no samples). One shared clock at division=4 makes a 16th-note grid; the pattern loops forever, instant sound, no transport. Toggle steps with /kick/step1../kick/step16 (and /snare/*, /hat/*); each step is boolean on/off. Ride tempo with /clock/tempo, lane volumes with the /kick_vol/in /snare_vol/in /hat_vol/in Good Buttons, and the overall tone with the /cutoff/in master-filter Good Button. Drums: kick = sine with a fast pitch-drop env; snare = noise + a tonal osc, both enveloped; hat = noise -> highpass filter -> short env.",
  "instrument": "groovebox",
